title: Grateful Dead Live at Warfield Theater on 1980-10-10
lineage: Nakamichi CM700 Mics (3)>Mixer>Sony D-5 Remaster: 1st Gen. Cassette>JVC TD-W309 (w/pitch correction)>Tascam DA-20mkII>Tascam CD-RW700
description: On The Road Again, It Must Have Been The Roses, Monkey & The Engineer, Jack A Roe, Dark Hollow, To Lay Me Down, Heaven Help The Fool, Bird Song, Ripple Mississippi Half Step, Franklin's Tower, Me & My Uncle, Big River, Candyman, Beat It On Down The Line, Row Jimmy, Minglewood Blues, Althea, Jack Straw Scarlet Begonias, Fire On The Mountain, Samson & Delilah, Big Railroad Blues, Estimated Prophet, Eyes Of The World, Drums, Truckin', Nobody's Fault But Mine, Black Peter, Around & Around, Promised Land, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Great Hotty Show!!!!!!!! This show is a gem among many here at the archive . Do yourself a major favor and download this show. Scarlet intro is just wat you look for in a kind Scarlet. RR, Est>eyes=sickness to the nth power. 

Get the show noooooooooow! 

PS. I only give shows a 5 if I was there. Can't do that here. Otherwise its a fine Gem of a show!
wow.. the jack straw this one is worth having JUST for the jack straw. this show is responsible for turning many many people on to the dead while I was in boarding school.

Althea > Jack Straw I went to the aforementioned school as well - both the Althea and Jack Straw are among the best versions ever - Jerry lays it down - anyone have the SBD? We had it high school circa 1981. Music is a 5 but I know the SBD smokes, so 4 total.

Crappy splices of sbd and distant audience Get a taste of a good audience around beginning of mwood which is hot it then goes into another sbd which is better quality. That said this is a great show with a hot Althea and Jack Straw just need a better copy. Scarlet>Fire is hot and I like the Big RR Blues in the middle...

One of the best promised lands ever.
once again this show is hot.  Jack Straw is probably my fav song and it just smokes on here, the Althea the precedes it is great too

scarlet/ fire we all have our favorite versions of songs and this scarlet-fire is mine...

this is a fantastic 1980 show, front to back...a true hidden gem...also check out Althea and Jack Straw, Black Peter and Estimated>Eyes, awesome acoustic set

Sounds like a board to me This is a less than crisp board, not an audience. Or am I wrong?

  It;s 10/10 95 today, so thought I 'd give show a try...Hot Franklins

Under 'Whole Show' gd80-10-10.sbd.cousinit.24710.sbefail.shnf_shn.zip	Shorten ZIP	1.1G

It is a Soundboard..

A Challenge Have a listen to the Althea and Jack Straw back to back a couple times. Then try to find a better version of each. I'm not talking sound quality....I'm talkin the boys having things dialed.
Lemme know what you find...I'm RRRREEEAAALLL curious.

This show is amazing Awesome set list. Awesome playing. Both sets are just absolutely stellar. I really love the Mississippi>Franklins opener. Also the Row Jimmy is a set one highlight in my opinion. 

From Althea on is the dead at their top form. Set two will have you out of your seat dancing at times, and in a trance at other times. Only the dead can do this to you. DEFINITELY check this show out!!! I don’t give out 5 stars lightly, but this one is worth it.

The Candyman is in town.. Acoustic Set 
5 stars>  but then again I think each and every 1980 acoustic set deserves that recognition.

Electric sets
4 stars> a whole entire 2 set show after the acoustic material WOW!
While the sound is good and lively there are times especially between songs that the dead air is a bit of a buzz kill.
also 1st electric set on sick bits has some level issues
from Row Jimmy to Minglewood
But bless our tapers, I can crank this with no problem!

Sweet Candyman
Jack Straw as a 1st electric set closer !

The pre-drums 3rd set is solid and thick especially considering 
they had already done two sets of music.
RXR Blues is another song 
that I undervalued until getting into the GD archives
great placement here
I have never heard Promised Land being the last rocker of the night
